H0.text: Having a height of 3,478 metres, Mount Mulhacen is the highest mainland point of which country. Italy

H1.text: Having a height of 3,478 metres, Mount Mulhacen is the highest mainland point of which country. Greece

H2.text: Having a height of 3,478 metres, Mount Mulhacen is the highest mainland point of which country. Croatia

H3.text: Having a height of 3,478 metres, Mount Mulhacen is the highest mainland point of which country. SPAIN

A4.text: Mulhacén is the highest mountain in peninsular Spain and in all of the Iberian Peninsula.

A5.text: Mulhacén is the highest peak in Southern Europe outside of the Alps.
